Package: gksu
Version: 2.0.0
Revision: 1

BuildDepends: libnautilus-ext1-dev (>= 2.20.0-1), startup-notification-dev, glitz, expat1, libpng3, cairo (>= 1.6-1), fontconfig2-dev (>= 2.4.1-1), freetype219 (>= 2.3.5-1), xft2-dev, pkgconfig (>= 0.21-1), x11-dev, atk1 (>= 1.20.0-1), glib2-dev (>= 2.14.0-1), gtk+2-dev (>= 2.12.0-1), pango1-xft2-ft219-dev (>= 1.18.4-4), pixman (>= 0.10.0-1), libiconv-dev, libgettext3-dev, gconf2-dev (>= 2.20.0-1), gnome-keyring-dev (>= 0.8.1-1), gtk-doc (>= 1.8-1), intltool (>= 0.36.0-1), libgksu2-dev, orbit2-dev (>= 2.14.9-1), gnome-vfs2-unified-dev, libgtop2.0.7-dev, dbus-dev, libxml2, libavahi-glib1-dev, avahi-dev
Depends: libgksu2, libnautilus-ext1-shlibs (>= 2.20.0-1)

Source: http://people.debian.org/~kov/%n/%n-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: f517302cff6f09e4f2f312c4b618bd40
SourceDirectory: %n-%v
PatchScript: perl -pi -e 's,-lutil,,' gksu/Makefile.in

ConfigureParams: --mandir=%p/share/man --disable-dependency-tracking --disable-schemas-install PKG_CONFIG_PATH="%p/lib/pango-ft219/lib/pkgconfig:%p/lib/fontconfig2/lib/pkgconfig:%p/lib/freetype219/lib/pkgconfig:$PKG_CONFIG_PATH" FREETYPE_CONFIG=%p/lib/freetype219/bin/freetype-config

InstallScript: make -j1 install DESTDIR=%d

DocFiles: AUTHORS COPYING ChangeLog po/ChangeLog:ChangeLog.po NEWS README

Description: GTK+ frontend to su and sudo
DescDetail: <<
  GKsu is a GTK+ frontend to the su program. It supports login shells and
  preserving environment variables, and is useful for launching graphical
  programs that need to run as another user. In the future, it will also
  wrap sudo.
<<
